<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - INSTALL - SLAVE VALVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SLAVE VALVE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If previously removed, install the air line fittings on the slave valve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021l7">Figure 217</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021l7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021l7" filename="../figg13/g13021l7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 217. Install Air Fittings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the spring on the shank of the actuating pin and insert in the bore of the
                transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021l8">Figure 218</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021l8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021l8" filename="../figg13/g13021l8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 218. Spring On Shank</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position gasket on the valve mounting surface and install the slave valve on the case,
                inserting the end of the actuating pin into the alignment sleeve (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021l9">Figure 219</hotlnk>). Secure the valve to the case with four bolts. Apply
                Loctite 242 or equivalent to the bolt threads. Tighten evenly to 8 to 12 ft-lbs. (11 to 16 N&#8226; m).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021l9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021l9" filename="../figg13/g13021l9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 219. Secure Valve To Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
